This repo sets configuration files for NEOVIM and TMUX.
*Does not install NEOVIM or TMUX.

############ INSTALLATION ############
1. Install tmux, neovim. Tmux is usually pre-installed.
2. Install xclip (ie 'sudo dnf install xclip' on RHEL).
3. Run `./setup.sh'

############# TMUX Issues #############
Keybinds are found in .tmux.conf.

The most annoying thing about tmux conf is the issues with yanking.
While in a tmux session:
1. Open select: Ctrl + q
2. Select line: Shift + v
3. Yank: y
4. Paste contents of your clipboard. 

If this did not work, try the below steps.
Verify xclip is working
> echo "test clipboard" | xclip -selection clipboard -in
If not, 
> echo $DISPLAY
You should see a display number, ex. ':0', ':1'
If not, set your display and reattach to tmux
1. > export DISPLAY=:0
2. Detach from session: <leader> d
3. Reattach to session (ex. > tmux attach -t 0)

############# NEOVIM ############
Must install a nerdfont like below then change terminal settings:
    wget -P ~/.local/share/fonts https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts/releases/download/v3.2.1/Lilex.zip \
    && cd ~/.local/share/fonts \
    && unzip Lilex.zip \
    && rm Lilex.zip \
    && fc-cache -fv

# Common problems
Cryptic treesitter problems can be solved by:
:TSInstall all and :TSUpdate

